<BaseLayout title="About Realspark">
  <h1>About Realspark</h1>

  <p>
    Realspark is a knowledge extraction platform. Every article gives you the most
    valuable 20% of a video, book, or research paper — in a 3 to 5 minute read.
  </p>

  <p>
    The goal is simple: you shouldn't have to watch a 45-minute video to get the three
    ideas that matter. Realspark does the extraction so you get the signal without the noise.
  </p>

  <h2>What you'll find here</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Daily Sparks</strong> — short summaries published regularly</li>
    <li><strong>Deep Sparks</strong> — long-form synthesis built from multiple related posts</li>
    <li><strong>Creator Pages</strong> — all summaries from one creator in one place</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How articles are written</h2>
  <p>
    Every article follows the same structure: hook, core ideas, the creator's perspective,
    an independent take, and actionable steps. No transcript dumps, no filler, no generic conclusions.
  </p>
</BaseLayout>
